    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102694</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A cake recipe includes the following ingredients: 2 cups of sugar, 5 cups of flour, and 1 cup of oil.</p>

<ol>
	<li>Draw a triple number line to represent the amount of each ingredient in 1, 2, 3, and 4 batches.</li>
	<li>If 20 cups of flour are used, how many batches of the recipe are made?</li>
	<li>If 20 cups of flour are used, how many cups of sugar and how many cups of oil are used?</li>
	<li>Jada wants to triple the recipe. She has 12 cups of flour. Is that enough?</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>A correct double number line will show sugar (cups): 0, 2, 4, 6, 8. Flour (cups): 0, 5, 10, 15, 20. Oil (cups): 0, 1, 2, 3, 4.</li>
	<li>4 batches</li>
	<li>8 cups of sugar and 4 cups of flour</li>
	<li>No, she will need 15 cups of flour.</li>
</ol>
</div>
